To limit the number of countries since many of the previous ones don't exist anymore, look for another property to use.
Check if there is any edge from "euro" to countries.
The intresting predicate is (wdt:P17), with label "country".
Same one I was using before..
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?p ?propertyName ?obj ?objName where { wd:Q4916 ?p ?obj. ?p sc:name ?propertyName. ?obj sc:name ?objName. FILTER(!isLiteral(?obj)) } LIMIT 100

6.narrative:
FINAL QUERY
consider only countries predicate (wdt:P17)
return the currency and number of countries.
6.query: SELECT DISTINCT ?currency ?currencyName (COUNT(DISTINCT ?country) as ?countries) where { ?s wdt:P38 ?currency. ?currency wdt:P17 ?country. ?s sc:name ?name. ?currency sc:name ?currencyName. ?country sc:name ?countryName. } GROUP BY ?currency ?currencyName HAVING (COUNT(DISTINCT ?country) > 1) LIMIT 100
